               <ce:legend>
                  <ce:simple-para id="tspara0015" view="all">LUS<ce:sup loc="post">$</ce:sup>: Landuse system; DFC: Dense forest cover, NAF: Non leguminous agroforestry, LAF: Leguminous agroforestry, WHF: Woody horticulture fruits, NHF: Non woody horticulture fruits, ALS: Agriculture lowland system, AUS: Agriculture upland system; ρ<ce:inf loc="post">b</ce:inf>: Soil bulk density; SCL: silty clay loam, SL: silty loam; DMRT: Duncan's Multiple Range Test values at <ce:italic>p</ce:italic> &lt; 0.05. Means in the column followed by different small letters in superscript (a-f) based on DMRT values represent statistical significant differences among the land uses at <ce:italic>p</ce:italic> &lt; 0.05. **Significant at <ce:italic>p</ce:italic> &lt; 0.0001; NS: Non-significant at <ce:italic>p</ce:italic> &lt; 0.05. Interaction effect of Lands use (LUS) and soil depth was significant only for pH at <ce:italic>p</ce:italic> &lt; 0.0001.</ce:simple-para>
               </ce:legend>
